<#
.SYNOPSIS
    CyberArk Privilege Cloud — Unified Power BI Dashboard Data Exporter (V6)
.DESCRIPTION
    Single-run, READ-ONLY script that authenticates to CyberArk ISPSS (Privilege
    Cloud SaaS), collects operational metrics, infrastructure health, and security
    risk data via REST APIs, and exports star-schema CSV files for Power BI.

    Combines the functionality of:
      - Pcloud_API_Dashboard_V2.ps1  (operational metrics)
      - CyberArk_HealthCheck.ps1     (infrastructure health)
      - Safe_Review.ps1              (safe security risk audit)

    Output Structure:
      Latest/    — Power BI data source (fixed filenames, overwritten each run)
      Archive/   — Historical snapshots (timestamped subfolders)

    All configuration parameters are at the TOP of the script (Sections A-K).
    Edit those sections freely; the runtime code below should not need changes.
.MODE
    READ-ONLY (GET requests only — no changes are made to CyberArk)
.NOTES
    Author   : Mohan C
    Version  : 6.0
    Requires : PowerShell 5.1+, CyberArk Privilege Cloud API access
               Service user needs: Privilege Cloud Administrator or Auditor role

    Changes since V5 (sections removed per request):
      - REMOVED System Health summary  (FACT_SystemHealth).
      - REMOVED Portal URL health       (FACT_PortalHealth).
      - REMOVED Active PSM sessions      (FACT_ActiveSessions).
      - REMOVED Connector stage entirely (DIM_Connector + FACT_ComponentHealth)
        — ComponentType came back empty in this environment.
      - REMOVED security risk findings   (FACT_RiskFindings and all risk-type
        detection). FACT_SafeMembers and FACT_AdminAudit are RETAINED.
      Output is now 14 CSVs (was 20). Vault Connectivity (CPM/PSM/AIM logon
      status) is KEPT.

    Changes in V5 (carried forward):
      - New SafeType classification (Section E) on DIM_Safe and FACT_Accounts:
          * "Personal Admin"    — safe name ends with -ADM (user-specific admin accts)
          * "Shared Admin"      — safe name ends with -T0/-T1/-T2 (shared tier admin accts)
          * "Standard Business" — any other non-default safe
          * "System/Default"    — CyberArk internal/default safes
      - Region is now optional: -ADM and -T0/-T1/-T2 safes are treated as
        naming-compliant even without a region prefix.
      - Tier for -ADM safes is extracted from the name when a T0/T1/T2 token is
        present, otherwise tagged "Personal/All-Tiers".

    Changes in V4 (carried forward):
      - Empty tables export a real header row (stable Power BI schema).
      - Get-Region requires a delimiter after a region prefix (no mis-tags).
      - Safe Members call uses includePredefinedUsers=true query parameter.
